Include <cuda/functional> for cuda::maximum / cuda::minimum.

reduce.cu has a libcudacxx-version-gated dispatch:

    #if defined(_LIBCUDACXX_CUDA_API_VERSION) && _LIBCUDACXX_CUDA_API_VERSION >= 2008000
                                     cuda::maximum<T>(),
    #else
                                     thrust::maximum<T>(),
    #endif

CUDA 12.9 / 13.0 ship libcudacxx 2.8.x / 3.0.x (both >= 2008000), so the
`cuda::maximum` branch is taken. That symbol lives in <cuda/functional>,
which reduce.cu doesn't include -- it only pulls in <thrust/functional.h>,
which used to forward-declare these but no longer does.

Adding the include lets the cuda::maximum/cuda::minimum names resolve.

--- a/catboost/cuda/cuda_util/kernel/reduce.cu
+++ b/catboost/cuda/cuda_util/kernel/reduce.cu
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
 #include <cub/device/device_reduce.cuh>
 #include <cub/device/device_segmented_reduce.cuh>

+#include <cuda/functional>
 #include <thrust/functional.h>

 namespace NKernel {
